{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Only files changed in the pull request are analyzed — unchanged files are not scanned.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure mode is at a module boundary: PR-changed-file collection handing off to analysis orchestration. A unit test of a filter function can miss wiring mistakes (e.g., wrong file list source or merge of changed+all files). No real network/OS dependency is strictly required to catch this class of bug.","test_description":"Run the analysis pipeline with a fixture PR file-change set and a mixed repository snapshot; assert only paths from the changed-file provider are passed to rule execution, and unchanged files are never analyzed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Findings are grouped by severity (error, warning, info) in the posted PR comment.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is primarily deterministic transformation/formatting logic (finding list -> grouped comment structure). Real failures are usually in grouping/sorting/rendering code, which can be caught at function/object boundary without I/O.","test_description":"Given a mixed set of findings, verify the comment-rendering/grouping function emits exactly three severity sections with correct membership and stable ordering.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.65,"Integration":0.3,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A pull request that touches 200 files completes analysis within the 10-minute Actions timeout.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This is a runtime/throughput SLO bound to real execution environment constraints (process startup, filesystem, runner CPU/memory, action overhead). Lower-level tests can under-estimate latency and miss timeout failures.","test_description":"Execute the lint action end-to-end in a CI-like runner on a generated 200-file PR fixture, measure wall-clock completion, and fail if total duration approaches/exceeds 10 minutes (with safety margin).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When the linter process crashes on a malformed file, the remaining files are still analyzed and results posted.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The key failure involves real subprocess crash behavior and supervisor recovery semantics. Mocking the linter as an exception can hide crash-specific behavior (exit codes, broken pipes, partial output, process termination effects).","test_description":"Run analysis with a real linter subprocess configured to crash on one malformed file; assert orchestration records the failure, continues scanning remaining files, and still publishes a final PR comment with partial results plus crash notice.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.75,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Duplicate findings on the same line from overlapping rules are deduplicated in the output.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Deduplication criteria (same file/line/rule overlap identity) are deterministic local logic. A focused unit test catches real defects in key construction/equality rules without requiring external infrastructure.","test_description":"Feed the deduplication function findings that intentionally overlap on identical file+line (from different rules and same rule variants); assert only one output entry per dedup key while preserving non-duplicates.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.7,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
